WEBVTT

00:00.080 --> 00:02.200
We're supposed to sit here
pissing in our pants

00:02.320 --> 00:04.215
while you decide our future, is that it?

00:04.376 --> 00:08.010
Why should the American taxpayers
support a lab that's in Toronto, Canada?

00:08.172 --> 00:10.722
Science is on the verge
of unlocking the secrets of life,

00:10.883 --> 00:13.660
and you're thinking about amputating
the only organization

00:13.780 --> 00:16.018
that's actually minding the store!
You're insane!

00:16.180 --> 00:18.480
How did you get this appointment?

00:18.641 --> 00:22.358
I slept with you for 25 years.
I suppose something rubbed off.

00:22.520 --> 00:23.378
Rachel.

00:24.544 --> 00:27.100
What we're doing...
I'm a little concerned.

00:27.220 --> 00:31.242
This thing that Carl is working on,
the magnetobacteria? It is insanity.

00:31.403 --> 00:34.579
You're worried about this...
magnetobacteria?

00:35.372 --> 00:38.541
I'm worried about somebody getting
a bullet in the back of the head.

00:38.873 --> 00:40.692
So bacteria forms a biofilm?

00:40.812 --> 00:42.879
Yes, but take a look at them
when we zoom in.

00:44.264 --> 00:46.508
- Like they're marching in formation.
- Precisely.

00:46.669 --> 00:48.510
Working together
to gum up the circuit board.

00:48.671 --> 00:49.844
As if programmed.

00:50.005 --> 00:53.297
I have high inter-ocular pressure
and an increased cup-to-disk ratio.

00:53.417 --> 00:55.934
The optic nerve in both eyes
is degenerating.

00:56.095 --> 00:58.311
I'm going blind, David. I'm sorry.

00:58.472 --> 01:01.606
We've been studying ways to repair
optic nerve damage for several years.

01:02.701 --> 01:05.860
However, when the procedure fails,
our test subjects

01:06.156 --> 01:08.279
are left totally blind.

01:08.440 --> 01:09.990
I don't want to do it, David.

01:11.722 --> 01:12.826
But I have to.

01:14.810 --> 01:17.288
All right, Bob, you can open them.

01:24.473 --> 01:25.547
I can see.

01:26.227 --> 01:28.199
Dr. Melnikov, Dr. Tran.

01:29.721 --> 01:32.715
- He was terrified.
- I didn't get that impression.

01:33.721 --> 01:34.982
It was obvious to me.

01:35.102 --> 01:38.146
People are talking.
They think you're acting differently,

01:38.471 --> 01:40.124
like you're, you know...

01:40.485 --> 01:42.638
more sensitive to their emotions.

01:42.974 --> 01:45.082
I don't know what's going on, David.

01:45.202 --> 01:47.318
All I do know
is that I don't want it to stop.

01:47.438 --> 01:50.499
I think some of the virus
traveled in the wrong direction,

01:50.735 --> 01:53.546
up the repaired optic nerve,
into Bob's brain

01:53.666 --> 01:55.660
and in particular
into his Jacobson's Organ.

01:56.583 --> 02:00.846
- He's smelling emotions.
- That would mean that Dr. Melnikov has

02:00.966 --> 02:04.777
genetically evolved
into a higher state of being.

02:04.897 --> 02:08.006
- Why would he just up and leave?
- Maybe somebody took him.

02:08.167 --> 02:10.604
- Do you know Olivier Roth?
- Of course I do.

02:10.725 --> 02:14.206
I never met him, but in the financial
circles he was with Buffet and Gates.

02:14.326 --> 02:16.975
Yeah, well, I think he's responsible
for magnetobacteria

02:17.095 --> 02:19.893
and I think he's kidnapped Bob,
so tell us where we can find him.

02:20.204 --> 02:22.607
We will change humanity,

02:22.727 --> 02:24.606
evolve the species.

02:24.767 --> 02:28.443
Listen to me, Roth, you son of a bitch.
You do anything to Bob, I'll find you.

02:28.604 --> 02:31.105
- See you in the future, David.
- Roth!

02:31.225 --> 02:35.283
You, Dr. Melnikov,
encompass the only hope we have left.

02:35.869 --> 02:38.578
A man
who truly understands the compassion,

02:39.135 --> 02:41.873
the hopes, the fears of his fellow man.

02:42.034 --> 02:44.292
Within you, in a stem cell

02:44.593 --> 02:46.002
in your brain,

02:46.163 --> 02:48.087
lies the future of mankind.

